    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Diagnostics (1991) - DIAGNOSTIC ANALYSIS - DIAGNOSTIC ANALYSIS PROCEDURES FOR -
        ...FUEL DILUTION OF LUBE OIL
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="0">
        <title>...FUEL DILUTION OF LUBE OIL</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">When fuel dilution is suspected, a quick determination can be made by using a
                <emph type="bold">Visagage</emph>
                (Figure 2.2). This instrument is used to compare the viscosity between used and new lubricating oil.
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Visagage,</emph>
                Model Two, can be purchased from:
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Louis C. Eitzen Co.</emph>
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">P.O. Box 1210</emph>
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Glenwood Springs, CO 81601</emph>
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">DB-2 Fuel Injection Pumps:</para>
            <para>Lubricating oil may be diluted by fuel oil passing from the drive shaft seals. A "weep" hole, located
                in the bottom of the pump housing, provides a method of detecting seal leakage, thus minimizing the
                possibility of fuel dilution of the crankcase oil.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
